f: TAKADA CORPORATION is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the plant business. The Company is engaged in the design, production, installation, piping, electric construction, instrumentation, maintenance and repair of various industrial facilities including steel, chemicals, petroleum, gas, electricity, nuclear power, marine development, city development, automobiles, communications, new materials, bio-technology, electronics, glass, food, medical and logistics, as well as water and waste treatment facilities and pollution control facilities. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries.

Seibu Electric Industry Co., Ltd. is mainly engaged in the information communication construction business. The Information Communication Construction segment is engaged in the design, construction and maintenance of optic fiber cable, network and mobile communication works, among others, as well as the sale of information communication materials and tools. The Solution segment is engaged in the construction of local area network (LAN) and wide area network (WAN), information security systems, as well as optic Internet protocol (IP) telephones, the development, maintenance and repair of software, the provision of total solutions, including information technology (IT) products consulting. The Others segment is engaged in civil engineering, electric, gas and drainage piping works, the design, construction and repair of clarification devices and garbage incinerators works, the transportation and equipment rental businesses, as well as the maintenance and sale of automobiles, among others.

Ifuji Sangyo Co., Ltd. is engaged in the egg-related business and seasonings-related business. The Company has three segments. The Eggs-related segment provides whole eggs, egg yolk and egg albumen, which are used by bakeries, confectioneries and perishable food vendors. The Seasoning segment manufactures powder and granule seasonings for commercial uses. The Others segment is involved in the leasing of real estate and the solar power generation business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had two subsidiaries.

THE TORIGOE CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the production and sale of flour products. The Company operates in three business segments. The Food segment produces flour products, including wheat flour, rye flour and bran, supplies premix flour for home and business uses, dry noodles and other processed food products, as well as produces and sells bread, confectioneries, raw noodles and other products. The Fodder segment manufactures and sells fodder products. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of storage services of agricultural products, as well as the transportation and logistics services for its raw materials and products. As of December 31, 2014, the Company had four subsidiaries.

Tama Home Co., Ltd. Is a Japan-based company which operates four business segments. The Residential Business is engaged in the contract of custom home and apartments building, the contract of renovation, and the agency of exterior construction and option construction work. The Real Estate segment involves the design, development and sale of mansion, sublease of office buildings and others. The Financial segment involves the fire insurance agency and financing for end users, as well as the provision of loan products. The Others segment includes overseas investment, furniture selling, construction of mansion and stores, ground investigation and soil improvement, advertisement agency, and the production, processing and sale of agricultural products.

Kirin Holdings Company, Limited is a holding company. The Company is engaged in alcohol beverages, non-alcohol beverages, and pharmaceuticals and bio-chemicals businesses. The Company's segments include Integrated Beverages, Pharmaceuticals and Bio-chemicals, and Others. Its Others segment includes food business, such as dairy products, and others. Its businesses comprise Japan Integrated Beverages, Overseas Integrated Beverages, and Pharmaceuticals and Bio-chemicals. The Japan Integrated Beverages business conducts manufacturing and sales of alcoholic beverages and non-alcoholic beverages in Japan. The Overseas Integrated Beverages business includes Lion Nathan Limited (Lion), Schincariol Participacoes e Representacoes S.A. (Brasil Kirin) and Myanmar Brewery Limited. The Pharmaceuticals and Bio-chemicals business includes Kyowa Hakko Kirin Co., Ltd., ProStrakan Group plc and Kyowa Hakko Bio Co., Ltd.

SAITA CORPORATION is engaged in the construction business and crushed stone business. The Construction segment is engaged in the acceptance of orders and construction of civil works, as well as the related transportation tasks. The Crushed Stone segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of crushed stones, the transportation of crushed stone products, as well as the quarry works. The Alcoholic Liquor segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of alcoholic liquor in Vietnam, as well as the import wholesale and retail of distilled spirits. The Others segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate, the sale of petroleum products, the environmental and security business, the manufacture and sale of fresh concrete, the sale of crushed stone products, as well as the transportation of general construction materials. As of June 30, 2012, the Company had nine subsidiaries and one associated company. In July 2013, it started solar power generation business.

FUJI P.S CORPORATION is a company mainly engaged in the operation of civil engineering works. The Company operates in four business segments. The Civil Engineering Work segment is engaged in the civil engineering works using prestressed concrete (PC) technology, as well as the manufacture and sale of PC products. The Construction segment is engaged in the construction works using PC technology, as well as the manufacture and sale of PC products. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing and management of real estate. The Others segment is engaged in the sale and leasing of construction materials and equipment. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had one subsidiary and one affiliated company.

KOATSU KOGYO CO., LTD. is a company mainly engaged in the designing, construction and supervision of civil engineering and construction activities that utilize pre-stressed concrete (PC) and general concrete. The Company has four business segments. The Construction segment is involved in the bridge and various concrete structure repair activities. The Concrete Product segment sells PC-related and general civil engineering concrete products, and leases metal molding forms. The Real Estate segment leases real estate with a focus on hotel facilities. The Others segment is engaged in the electric power distribution business and food products business. As of September 30, 2014, the Company had two subsidiaries.

HIGASHIMARU CO., LTD. is principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of formulated feeds for fish breeding. The Company operates in two business segments. The Seafood segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of formulated feeds for fish culturing. The Food segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of dry noodles, instant noodles, bowl udon (Japanese wheat noodle) and sauces for noodles, as well as curry, jams and seasonings. On July 31, 2013, it fully acquired an Osaka-based company, Mukai Chinmido.

COCA-COLA WEST COMPANY, LIMITED is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of drinks. The Company operates in three business segments. The Cold Beverage segment is engaged in the production and sale of drinks, as well as the vending machine, real estate and insurance agency related business. The Healthcare and Skincare segment produces and sells health food and cosmetics. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of copying, information and optical equipment. As of December 31, 2014, the Company had 15 subsidiaries and four associated companies.

Takeda Pharmaceutical Company Limited is a Japan-based company engaged in the pharmaceutical business. The Ethical Pharmaceutical segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of pharmaceutical products, such as therapeutic substances for diabetes, circulatory drugs, anticancer drugs, drugs for central neurological diseases, digestive system drugs, hormonal agents, osteoporosis drugs, antibiotic agents, allergy medications, vitamin drops and vaccines, among others. The Healthcare segment manufactures and sells general drugs and medicines, as well as quasi drugs. The Others segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of reagents, clinical diagnostics and chemical products. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 146 subsidiaries and 17 associated companies.

SK home Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the detached residential business. The Company is engaged in the planning, design, sale, construction and supervision of custom homes such as residential houses, condominiums and others. The Company is also engaged in the real estate sale business, and the renovation and remodeling businesses in association with the detached residential business.

OCHI HOLDINGS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based holding company primarily engaged in the building material household equipment sale business. The Company has three business segments. The Building Material Household Equipment Sale segment is engaged in the purchase and wholesale of housing related materials. The Life segment is involved in the purchase and sale of household goods such as heating equipment and others to supermarkets, home centers and drug stores. The Processing segment is engaged in the purchase of building materials, as well as the processing, assembly and sale of precursor structures mainly for wooden houses.

MARUTAI CO., LTD. is a food manufacturing company. The Company is primarily engaged in the production and sale of various flavored ramen bars, noodle dishes, instant cup noodles and other related products. The Company distributes its products through wholesalers, retailers and supermarkets.

SYSKEN Corporation, formerly Nishinippon System Installations and Construction Co., Ltd., is mainly engaged in the electric communication facility construction business. The Information Electric Communication segment is engaged in the electric communication facility designing and construction business for NTT Group, and the creation of other information electric communication-related infrastructures. The Integrated Facility segment is engaged in the communication facility and electric facility construction businesses for private companies and government offices. The Others segment is engaged in the sale of communication materials and equipment; the development, manufacture and sale of electric communication equipment; the design, development, sale and maintenance of software; the provision of transportation services for communications construction materials, and the leasing of communication equipment, office automation (OA) equipment and vehicles, among others.

Nisshinbo Holdings Inc. is a holding company with seven segments. The Textile segment manufactures and sells textile products. The Break Products segment provides beak assemblies and friction materials for automobile breaks. The Paper segment offers household paper products, such as tissue paper, kitchen towel, fine paper and artificial paper. The Precision Machine segment involves in the manufacture and sale of mechatronic products, precision parts processing, plastic molding. The Chemical segment offers rigid urethane foam, carbon products, high-performance chemicals. The Electronics segment offers wireless communication equipment, electronic components and others. The Real Estate segment leases buildings and shopping centers, as well as sells residential land. In addition, the Company is also engaged in the wholesale of food, industrial materials and clothing fibers, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 91 subsidiaries and 112 associated companies.

Business One Holdings, Inc. is primarily engaged in real estate-related business. The Real Estate segment is engaged in purchase, design, brokerage and bidding business of land and buildings targeted at real estate funds and developers. The Condominium Management segment is engaged in condominium management business. The Rental segment is engaged in rental business of the real estate held by the Company, and rental brokerage business. The Software segment is engaged in development of software and sale of software packages. The Finance segment primarily provides real estate secured loans for corporations. The Others segment is engaged in providing management guidance and business support for subsidiaries.

Ube Industries, Ltd. is a Japan-based chemical manufacturer. The Chemical and Resin segment manufactures and sells caprolactam, nylon, industrial chemicals, synthetic rubber, ammonia, ammonium sulfate and nylon resin, among others. The Functional Product and Fine segment offers functional materials, electronic- and information communications-related products and phenol resin. The Pharmaceutical segment offers pharmaceutical products. The Construction Material segment provides cement, limestone and construction materials. The Machinery and Metal Forming segment offers industrial machinery, hydraulic equipment, marine equipment and molded articles. The Energy and Environmental segment sells coal, operates call centers and sells electric power. The Others segment involves in the development, purchase, sale and leasing of real estate. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 146 affiliated companies.

GRANDES, Inc. is a real estate company mainly engaged in the construction and sale of residential properties. The Company operates in three business divisions. The Sale of Speculative House division is involved in the planning, development and provision of wooded detached houses named FORLUX in Oita City and Beppu City, and the planning, development and provision of RESCO series condominiums for investment and LUXIN series condominiums for sale, which aim at high-net-worth individuals, and young families and singles, respectively. The Construction Subcontracting division involves in the contracted construction of wooden detached houses for rent and general housing, as well as the contracting of various renovation works. The Others division involves in the subleasing of borrowed wooden detached housing, which were constructed by itself.

Isetan Mitsukoshi Holdings Ltd. is a Japan-based holding company mainly engaged in department store business. The Company has five business segments. The Department Store segment is engaged in the operation of general department stores in Japan domestic markets and overseas markets. The Credit, Finance and Association of Friends segment is involved in businesses related to credit card, money lending, nonlife and life insurance agency, among others. The Retail and Special Store segment is engaged in the sale of women’s clothing, the manufacture of food and the operation of super markets. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing, management and maintenance of real estate. The Others segment is involved in businesses related to manufacturing, import and export, wholesale, logistics, human resources, as well as information processing services, among others.

HISAMITSU PHARMACEUTICAL CO., INC. is a pharmaceutical company that operates in two business segments. The Medical and Related Product segment, along with its subsidiaries and associated companies, mainly manufactures and sells pharmaceuticals and related products in Japan, as well as the United States, Brazil, Vietnam, China and Indonesia. The Others segment is engaged in the urban cable television broadcasting business and Internet connection service business, the sale and rearing of experimental animals, the sale of experimental equipment and materials, the purchase, manufacture and sale of packing materials, the non-life insurance agency business and advertising agency business, among others.

TRUCK-ONE CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the commercial vehicles related and transportation related businesses. The Company operates in two business segments. The Commercial Vehicles Related segment sells trucks, dump cars, special vehicles (cement mixer trucks, freezing cars, tank cars, in-vehicle cars and vehicles for work at height set), releases freezing cars and freezing containers, as well as provides inspection, maintenance and repair services for cars. The Transportation segment operates transportation business through its subsidiaries. As of December 31, 2012, the Company had two subsidiaries and one associated company.

TRUST Holdings Inc. is a pure holding company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, is principally engaged in parking lot operation and real estate related businesses. The Company operates through three business segments. The parking lot business segment is engaged in the operation of parking lots that were built from idle lands. The real estate business segment is engaged in the planning, development and sale of real estates, focusing on apartments for families. The others segment consists of security services related to parking lots. On September 27, 2013, the Company transferred two wholly owned subsidiaries to another wholly owned subsidiary TRUST PARK. On November 15, 2013, the Company established a wholly owned subsidiary in Fukuoka, Japan, which is engaged in medical institution related service.

NIPPON KANRYU INDUSTRY CO., LTD. is a Japan-based construction company. The Company operates in three business segments. The Construction segment is engaged in the construction of traffic safety facilities, slopes and environmental maintenance works. This segment is also engaged in the sale of traffic safety facility materials and construction materials. The Disaster Prevention Safety segment is engaged in the sale of disaster prevention safety and sanitary products, as well as security products. The Chemical segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of insoluble sulfur products and other construction materials. As of September 30, 2013, the Company had two consolidated companies.

KYUDENKO CORPORATION is a provider of facilities engineering services. The Company operates in two business segments. The Facilities Engineering segment is engaged in the design and construction of electric works, including power distribution lines, interior wiring and electrical communications works, in addition to the conditioning pipe works, such as air-conditioning, cooling and heating, plumbing sanitary and water treatment works. The Others segment is engaged in the sale of electrical work and air conditioning ductwork related materials and equipment, the sale of real estate, the operation of golf courses, the development of software and other businesses, including the wind electricity, medical related and the manpower dispatching businesses.

TAISEI CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the sale of food packaging materials and food materials. The Company sells food packaging materials and food materials to confectionery stores, box lunch shops and individuals through mail-orders based on Internet, fax machines and telephones. Through its subsidiaries, the Company is also engaged in the manufacture of food materials related to confectioneries and bread, as well as the manufacture and sale of food material processed products. As of September 30, 2012, the Company had two consolidated subsidiaries. On January 4, 2014, the Company established a wholly owned subsidiary in Tokyo.

TAIHEIYO CEMENT CORPORATION is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture of cement products. The Company operates in six business segments. The Cement segment manufactures and sells cement and ready-mixed concrete. The Resources segment offers mined aggregates and limestone products. The Environmental segment is engaged in the recycling of waste materials. The Construction Materials and Civil Engineering segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of secondary concrete products, construction materials and chemical products, as well as the engineering and construction business. The Ceramics and Electronics segment offers ceramic and electronic products. The Others segment is engaged in the real estate, engineering, information processing, financial, transportation and warehousing, as well as sports and other businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 234 subsidiaries and 103 associated companies.

Mitsui Matsushima Co., Ltd. is primarily engaged in coal sales business. The Coal Sales segment involves the import trading and brokerage of coal products. The brokerage segment provides settlement services and related services regarding coal import. The Coal Production segment is involved in the investment, 1111 Of com sit sites. The Food-use material segment involves in the manufacture of straw and sale of food-use materials. Thank Alloy Iron segment operates recycling and alloy iron business. The Others segment involves in propane gas distribution business, operation and Management Contracting Business segment involves in the contracting operation of accommodation facilities and recreation facilities. The Construction Machinery and Material segment is engaged in the sale of construction materials and machinery, Contracting Φ æ1woemn we are famiy

OBAYASHI CORPORATION is primarily engaged in construction business. The Company operates in five segments. The Domestic Construction segment is involved in the contracting of construction work and related business in Japan. The Oversea Construction segment is involved in the contracting of construction work and related business oversea. The Domestic Civil Engineering segment is involved in the contracting of civil engineering and related business in Japan. The Oversea Civil Engineering segment is involved in the contracting of civil engineering and related business oversea. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the buying and selling of Real Estate, leasing and development projects of residential land, as well as other related business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 85 subsidiaries and 27 associated companies.

NIPPON STEEL & SUMITOMO METAL CORPORATION is a steel company. Its Steel Manufacturing segment engages in the manufacture and sale of steel bars, pipes and secondary steel products. Engineering segment engages in the construction of steel manufacturing plants, industrial machinery and furnaces, and environmental facilities. Chemical segment offers pitch coke, naphthalene, phthalic anhydride, carbon black and materials for liquid crystal displays (LCDs). New Material segment offers rolled metal foils and bonding wires for semiconductors. System Solution segment provides engineering consultation services on computer systems. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 337 subsidiaries and 109 associated companies.

mbs, inc. is principally engaged in the design and construction of buildings, as well as the real estate business. The Company has four business segments. The Home Makeup segment is engaged in the repair and renovation of the interior and exterior works of various buildings, utilizing its home makeup method. The Construction Work segment conducts new building construction and renovation works, utilizing general construction methods. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the sale, leasing and brokerage of real estate. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of know-how services and the sale of materials, such as paints.

TOTO LTD. is engaged in the manufacture and sale of restroom fixtures, bathroom fixtures, kitchen fixtures and others. The Company operates in four business segments. The Domestic Housing Facility segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of rest room products, such as sanitary chinaware, warm wash toilets, and plastic and rubber formed parts; bath, kitchen and wash products, such as plastic bathtubs, unit bath rooms, water faucet hardware and parts, among others. The Oversea Housing Facility segment offers products for restroom, bath and basin use. The New Field segment provides tiles and ceramic products, as well as manufactures and sells tile construction materials and coating materials. The Others segment is engaged in the real estate leasing business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 53 subsidiaries and five associated companies.

Toubujyuhan Co.,Ltd. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in real estate business. It has four business segments. The Real Estate Trading segment involves in the sale of properties owned by the Company, and the brokerage sale of properties owned by others. The Real Estate Rental segment involves in the brokerage sale and rental management business of properties owned by other companies, as well as the sale of properties owned by the Company. The Real Estate-related segment involves in the contracting of remodeling of properties, agency sale of insurance such as fire insurance, as well as real estate-related goods sale through Internet. The Others segment involves in the sale of welfare related goods, the agency sale of mobile phones and others.

DOWA HOLDINGS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based holding company. The Company has six business divisions. The Environment and Recycling division is engaged in the operation of waste management, recycling, soil remediation and logistics businesses. The Smelting division manufactures and sells copper, zinc, gold, silver and other metals. The Electronic Materials division manufactures and sells electrical conducting material for electronic component, among others. The Metal Processing division manufactures and sells processed metal products, circuit boards. The Thermal Treatment division is engaged in the thermal treatment and surface treatment processing of metal materials, as well as the manufacture, sale and maintenance of thermal processing facilities and auxiliary facilities. The Others division is engaged in the real estate leasing business, plant construction works business and others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 89 subsidiaries and 19 associated companies.

OHISHI SANGYO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of packaging-related materials. The Company operates in three business segments. The Cushioning Function Materials segment mainly manufactures and sells pulpy molds, corrugated boards and other materials with cushioning function. The Packaging Function Materials segment mainly manufactures and sells packaging-related materials, including paper bags and synthetic resin products. The Others segment is involved in the sale of information processing equipment, the development and sale of software and design-related business, as well as the leasing of real estate properties.

SANIX INCORPORATED is a Japan-based company that mainly engaged in the sanitation management business. The Company operates in three business divisions. The Home Sanitation (HS) division is engaged in the termite control construction, basic maintenance, repair and reinforcement, underfloor and ceiling ventilation systems construction, as well as photovoltaic generation systems construction and related equipment wholesale. The Establishment Sanitation (ES) division is involved in the maintenance and construction of building water supply and drainage equipment, as well as photovoltaic generation systems construction. The Environmental Resources Development division is engaged in the intermediate process such as recycling of industrial wastes, as well as the power generation and sales business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 11 consolidated subsidiaries.

KOSE R.E. Co., Ltd. is a real estate company. The Company operates in three business segments. The Family Condominium Sales segment is engaged in the planning, development and sale of condominiums in Tokyo and central cities of Kyushu and other prefectures. The Asset Management Condominium Sales segment is engaged in the planning, development and sale of condominiums in central location of Fukuoka. The Real Estate Leasing and Management segment is engaged in the leasing, management and brokerage of condominiums for asset management purpose. On July 17, 2013, it acquired a property in Fukuoka. On February 1, 2014, the Company acquired 100% stake of R-Maintenance co ltd. On February 25, 2014, the Company acquired a property in Fukuoka.

Bridgestone Corporation is engaged in developing, manufacturing and marketing tires and diversified products. The Company operates through two segments: Tires and Diversified Products. The Company's Tires segment offers tires for passenger cars, trucks, buses, motorcycles, construction and mining vehicles, aircraft, and motor cycles, as well as tubes, wheels and related accessories. The Tires segment also includes the retreading business, and automotive maintenance services. The Company's Diversified Products segment offers various categories of products, including chemical products, industrial products, automotive components, construction materials, electronic equipment, sporting goods and bicycles. Many of these products are made from rubber or rubber-derived materials. The Company has over 170 manufacturing plants in approximately 30 countries around the world. It sells products in over 150 countries across the world.

Mobile Create Co., Ltd. is principally engaged in the development and sale of mobile application system. The Company operates as an automobile network operator, developing automobile management system for road passenger carriers, including taxi operators and bus operators, as well as logistics companies, such as trucking operators. The Company develops automobile management system utilizing infrastructure of packet communication through global positioning system (GPS) and land mobile radio (LMR), or the Internet and third generation network. The Company also provides related communication and application services and maintenance services. The Company generates its revenue from three divisions, including appliance, automobile network, and customized service. On March 1, 2013, the Company established a Okinawa-based wholly owned subsidiary.

FUJI ELECTRIC CO., LTD. is a manufacturer of industrial equipment. Power Generation and Social Infrastructure division provides thermal, geothermal and hydroelectric power generation equipment, energy management systems and nuclear-related equipment, among others. Industrial Infrastructure division offers industrial drive systems, measurement systems, industrial power systems and others. Power Electronics segment provides inverters, servo, motors and uninterruptible power supply (UPS), among others. Electronic Device segment offers power semiconductors, photoconductors and solar cells. Food Distribution segment offers food and beverage vending machines, distribution systems and currency-related equipment. Others segment engages in the real estate, insurance agency, travel businesses, as well as the provision of financial, printing and information and temporary staffing services. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 98 subsidiaries and 27 associated companies.

Showa Manufacturing Co., Ltd. is a manufacturing company that operates in three business segments. The Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of air conditioning equipment, including fan coil units and air handling units, among others; heat source equipment, including boilers, heaters and burners, among others; environmental equipment, including circular hot bath equipment, air purifiers and others, as well as heat treat furnace for liquid crystal panel manufacturing use. The Material Processing segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of landscaping products including bridge rails and safety barriers, as well as ductile cast iron and special alloy cast products. The Service Engineering segment engages in contract construction work for air conditioning and plumbing sanitary.

Sumitomo Electric Industries, Ltd. is a Japan-based manufacturing company. It has five segments. The Automobile-related segment offers wire harnesses, rubber cushions, hoses for automobiles, automobile electrical parts and others. The Information Communications-related segment offers fiber-optic cables, electrical cables and equipment for communications use, optical communications-related parts and others. The Electronics-related segment offers electronic wires, compound semiconductors, flexible print circuit boards, fluorine resin products and others. The Environment Energy-related segment is engaged in the provision of conductive products, electric wire cables and equipment, coil wires and air springs, as well as the electrical construction works. The Industrial Material and Other segment offers steel wires for precision springs, steel rods, carbide tools and optical parts for lasers.

MISUMI CO., LTD. is a diversified company mainly operates in three business segments. The Energy segment involves in the wholesale and retail of petroleum-related products such as gasoline, diesel oil, heating oil, heavy oil, lube oil, liquefied petroleum (LP) gas, appliances, distribution and filling of LP gas, and construction and inspection of high-pressure gas equipment. The Lifestyle segment involves in the sale of books, Compact Discs (CDs), television games, personal computers and cellular phones, videos and CD rental business, the sale, maintenance, safety inspection of automobiles, commercial complex operation, and the sale of automobile tires, among others. The Food and Beverage segment sells Kentucky Fried Chicken, manufactures and sells mineral water. It also involves in advertising agency and golf courses operation businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 12 subsidiaries, one associated company and one affiliated company.
