Nishi-Nippon Financial Holdings, Inc. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the operation and management of bank subsidiaries. Nishi-Nippon City Bank, Ltd. is engaged in banking business, which provides various financial products and services through deposit business, lending business, exchange business, securities investment business. It also operates financial related other business. The Bank of Nagasaki, Ltd is engaged in banking business. Nishi Nippon Shinyo Hosho K.K. is engaged in Credit guarantee business.

The Bank of Okinawa, Ltd. is a regional bank. The Bank, along with its subsidiaries, operates in three business segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the offering of financial services, such as deposit, loan, domestic and foreign exchange transactions, marketable securities investment services, as well as sale of government bonds and trust businesses. The Leasing segment provides leasing services. The Others segment is engaged in the consolidation and accounting of cash, the acquisition and sale of real estate properties for auction, the investigation and research of financial economics, the credit guarantee business, the credit card business, the computer-related business and others.

Bank of The Ryukyus, Limited (the Bank) is a Japan-based regional bank mainly engaged in the provision of financial services for individual and corporate customers The Bank operates in three business segments. Banking business includes deposit business, lending business, domestic exchange business, and foreign exchange business, among others. The Credit Card business provides the consumer financial services and settlement for merchants and individuals. The Credit Guarantee business engages in the assurance business, such as housing loans. In addition, the Bank is also involved in the secretary-agency business, cash scrutiny organize business, research businesses related to industry, economy and finance, as well as leasing business. AS of March 31, 2014, the Bank had 5 subsidiaries and one associated company.

Kyushu Railway Company is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in transportation, construction, station buildings and real estate, distribution and food business, as well as other business around Kyushu in Japan. The Company has 4 business segments. Transportation segment operates railway business, bus business, marine business and car rental business. Construction segment operates construction business, vehicle mechanical equipment engineering business, and electrical construction business. Station Buildings and Real Estate segment engages in leasing of station buildings and other real estate, as well as sale of condominium unit and other real estate. Distribution and Food segment engages in retail industry, catering industry and agriculture industry.

The Eighteenth Bank, Limited (the Bank) is a regional bank that operates in four business segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the provision of banking services, such as loan, deposit, securities trading, securities investment, domestic exchange, foreign exchange, corporate bond trustee business and registration services, among others. The Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of personal properties and other property rights. The Guarantee segment is engaged in the guarantee of housing and consumer loan-related debt obligations. The Others segment is engaged in the credit card business, the provision of computer services, the survey and research business, as well as the entrusted business. As of March 31, 2014, the Bank had six consolidated subsidiaries.

The Okinawa Electric Power Company, Incorporated is a company mainly engaged in the electric power industry. The Company operates in two business segments. The Electrical Power segment is engaged in the electrical power supply in Okinawa. The Others segment consists of the contract construction of electrical distribution, electric, civil engineering and construction works, the research and design of electrical facilities and construction inspection, the environmental and geological research, and land survey, the installation works of air conditionings, sanitation equipment and electrical water heaters, the sale and manufacture of electrical machinery and instruments, the rental of cars and supplies, the operational management of computers, the data centre and contact centre businesses, the management, purchase, sale and leasing of land and buildings, the wind power generation business, as well as the setting, operation and maintenance of off-grid power systems, among others.

GREENLAND RESORT COMPANY LIMITED is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the leisure business. The Company operates in six business segments. The Amusement Park segment operates amusement parks, restaurants in amusement parks and ski resorts. The Golf Course segment operates golf courses. The Hotel segment operates hotels. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the purchase, sale and leasing of real estate properties. The Civil Engineering and Construction Material segment is involved in the civil engineering work, as well as the manufacture, sale and transportation of construction materials. The Others segment is engaged in the life and damage assurance agency business, the manpower dispatching business, as well as the manufacture, supply and sale of city gas. As of December 31, 2013, the Company had three subsidiaries and one affiliated company.

THE HOWA BANK, LTD. is regional bank principally engaged in the provision of financial services. The Bank mainly operates its business through the Banking segment. The Banking segment is involved in the provision of financial services, including banking services and securities business, as well as the counter sale of investment trust and insurance products, among others.

TOHO CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in movie, theater and real estate businesses. The Movie segment is engaged in the production, distribution and showing of movies, as well as the production and sale of visual software. The Theater segment is engaged in the production and showing of theaters. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing, maintenance and management of real estate, as well as the management, cleaning and repair of roads. The Others segment is engaged in other business activities, including the operation of entertainment facilities, shops and restaurants, the provision of accounting consulting and guidance services, as well as the operation and management of fee-charging nursing homes and group homes.

ONOKEN CO., LTD. is principally involved in the sale of steel products. The Company sells a variety of steel products, such as steel plates, steel shapes and steel bars, as well as construction materials and machinery through its subsidiaries located in Kyushu and Chugoku area, Kansai and Chukyo area, as well as Kanto and Tohoku area. The Company is also engaged in the operation of contracted construction business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had three consolidated subsidiaries and one unconsolidated subsidiary.

Seibu Electric & Machinery Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of industrial machinery. The Company operates in three business segments. The Conveying Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of aluminum products, laser microanalysis (LM) guide and other conveying equipment. The Industrial Machinery segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of bearings, ball clinchers, LM guide and other industrial machinery. This segment is also engaged in the coating and assembly of its products through its subsidiaries. The Others segment is engaged in the sale of machinery components and multilevel parking equipment, as well as the operation of parking lots. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had four subsidiaries.

Ricoh Company, Ltd. is engaged in integrated domestic and overseas manufacturing services. The Company's segments include Imaging & Solutions, Industrial Products and Other. The Company's Imaging & Solutions segment is engaged in office imaging, production printing and network system solutions. The Company's Industrial Products segment is engaged in manufacturing and sales of thermal media, optical equipment, semiconductors, electronic component and Inkjet head. Its Other segment is engaged in manufacturing and sales of digital cameras, financing business and logistics services provided through the Company's subsidiaries. It offers various services, which include business process services, communication services, managed document services, sustainability management services workplace services, information technology (IT) infrastructure services and application services. It offers industry solution to various sectors, which include healthcare, higher education and financial services.

IHI Corporation manufactures an enormous range of products. The Resources, Energy and Environment division provides boilers, storage facilities, nuclear power equipments. The Social Infrastructure and Marine division provides bridges, floodgates, shield machines and marine structures, as well as operates real estate business. The Industrial System and General Machinery division provides marine machinery, logistics systems, transportation machinery, parking, steel machinery, industrial machinery, among others. The Aerospace and Defense division provides aviation engine, rocket systems and space utilization, defense equipment systems and others. The Others division provides communication, electronic, electrical measurement, information processing equipments and devices, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 148 subsidiaries and 35 associated companies.

KYUSHU LEASING SERVICE CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the leasing and installment business. The Company operates in five business segments. The Leasing and Installment segment is engaged in the leasing and installment sale of machinery and equipment. The Financing segment is engaged in the leasing of cash and the purchase of debts. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing and sale of real estate, as well as the investment in anonymous associations. The Fee Business segment is engaged in the soliciting of life insurance, the agency for automobile leasing, the provision of real estate-related services, as well as the nonlife insurance agency business. The Others segment is engaged in the electric power sales business, as well as the goods sales business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had nine subsidiaries.

IZUTSUYA CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the operation of department stores. The Company operates in three business segments. The Department Store segment is engaged in the operation of department stores, the operation of restaurants in department store, the sale of gifts, the sale of merchandises to external customers, the wholesale of domestic and imported products, the cleaning of stores, the management of parking lots and real estate, as well as the leasing of shops and offices. The Association segment is engaged in the sale of prepaid products. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of information processing services. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and two associated companies.

SANKEI CHEMICAL CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of agrichemicals, as well as the agrichemical-related pest control business. The Agrichemicals and Agrichemical-related segment offers its agrochemical products and purchased products to Economic Federation of Agricultural Cooperatives and Agricultural Cooperatives through National Federation of Agricultural Cooperative Associations, as well as to others through trading companies, specified agents and its associated company. As of November 30, 2013, the Company had two subsidiaries and one associated company.

KROSAKI HARIMA CORPORATION is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the manufacture of refractory materials. The Company operates in five business segments. The Refractory segment manufactures and sells refractory products. This segment is also involved in the manufacture and maintenance of refractory manufacturing facilities and the distribution business. The Furnace segment designs, constructs and repairs furnaces. The Ceramics segment manufactures and sells fine ceramic products for various industries. This segment also sells landscape materials. The Real Estate segment leases stores and warehouses. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of lime for steel mills. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 10 consolidated subsidiaries and three associated companies.

SAIBU GAS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based gas supplier engaged in four business segments. The Gas segment is engaged in the manufacture, supply and distribution of gas, the collection of gas bills, the construction of gas plumbing, the examination of gas equipment and others. The Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) segment is engaged in the sale of LPG and LPG equipment, as well as the LPG-related construction works. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing and sale of real estate, as well as residential real estate development and construction. The Others segment is involved in the heat supply business, the operation of nursing homes, the provision of information processing services, the operation of restaurants, amusement parks and golf courses, the general maintenance and management of buildings, as well as the manufacture and sale of instant noodles, among others.

Maruto Sangyo Co. Ltd. is engaged in the manufacture and sale of packaging materials, including compound film materials and single film materials, as well as the purchase and sale of packaging containers. Through its subsidiaries, the Company is also engaged in the sale of single film materials and packaging containers in Hong Kong and Mainland China, as well as the manufacture of packaging materials. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had two subsidiaries.

THE BANK OF SAGA LTD. is a Japan-based regional bank. The Bank is involved in the provision of financial services, including deposit business, lending business, domestic and foreign exchange businesses, securities trading business and securities investment business, as well as other services. The Others segment involves in the provision of banking and financial related services, such as outsourcing services, temporary staffing services, information processing services, credit guarantee services, leasing services and venture capital services, as well as fund businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and two associated companies.

DAIHEN Corporation is engaged in the manufacture, sale and repair of various transformers, welding machines, industrial robots, high frequency power and clean transport robots. The Company operates in four business segments. The Electrical Power Equipment segment manufactures, sells and repairs various transformers, power receiving and distribution facilities, switches, monitoring and control systems, as well as dispersed power equipment. The Welding and Mechatronic segment provides electrical welding machines, plasma cutting machines, industrial air cleaners, industrial robots and others. The Semiconductor-related Equipment segment offers high frequency power, clean transport robots and others. The Others segment is involved in the real estate leasing business. As of March 31, 2014, it had 37 subsidiaries and seven associated companies.

Nippon Tungsten Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the powder metallurgy business. The Company operates in two business segments. The Powder Metallurgy segment manufactures and sells tungsten and molybdenum wires, bars and boards, electrical contacts, electrodes, magnetic head substrates, ultra-precise processed products, machinery parts for semiconductors and liquid crystals, die cutters, cutting tools, wear and corrosion resistant parts, machinery parts and shield materials, among others. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of industrial machinery, the management of real estate properties, the provision of insurance agency services, as well as the sale of commodities. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had eight subsidiaries and one associated company.

OKANO VALVE MFG.CO.LTD., formerly OKANO VALVE MFG. CO., is a Japan-based manufacturing company. The Company operates in two business segments. The Valve segment casts and process materials, as well as manufactures nuclear power valves and general valves for electric generation plants. The Maintenance segment is engaged in the periodic valve inspection and valve repair works. As of November 30, 2014, the Company had one subsidiary and one associated company.

West Japan Railway Company is mainly engaged in the provision of passenger railway transportation services. The Company operates in four business segments. The Transportation segment provides ferry and bus transportation services. This segment also offers railway services, such as Sanyo Shinkansen and conventional express railway lines throughout the Hokuriku, Chugoku, Kinki and Northern Kyushu areas. The Distribution segment is engaged in the operation of department stores in Osaka Station Building and Kyoto Station Building. This segment is also involved in the retail and restaurant businesses in major stations. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the sale and leasing of real estate properties it owns, as well as the operation of shopping centers. The Others segment is engaged in the hotel, travel, automobile rental, advertising, electric construction, information service and other businesses.

RINGER HUT CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the operation of chain restaurants. The Company operates through four business segments. The Nagasaki Chanpon segment operates chain restaurants under the name Nagasaki Chanpon (Nagasaki Prefecture-style noodles). The Tonkatsu segment is engaged in the operation of tonkatsu (Japanese-style pork cutlets) chain restaurants. The Japanese Food segment is engaged in the operation of local cuisine restaurants in Nagasaki Prefecture, under the name Nagasaki Shippoku. The Facility Maintenance segment is mainly engaged in the provision of maintenance services for its chain restaurant facilities.

SEIKO ELECTRIC CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the development, production and sale of electric systems and equipment. The Company has four business segments. The Electric Power segment manufactures and sells electric power control systems, electric power switchgears, automated power distributing machines, electric power operation informatization equipment and others. The Environment and Energy segment mainly offers public and environmental systems, industrial plant systems, power receiving and transformation systems, storage battery systems, as well as the construction and engineering related to its products. The Information segment mainly provides active server pages (ASP) service, system integration and e-learning services. The Others segment offers general electrical goods and business support services, and other control equipment. As of December 31, 2014, the Company had seven subsidiaries and one associated company.

GREEN CROSS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the sale and rental of safety equipment, as well as the production and sale of sign media. The Company is principally involved in the sale and rental of safety equipment, such as road safety materials, disaster prevention materials for construction, security and safety products and protective equipment for construction companies, real estate companies, advertising companies, public offices, schools and other general companies. Its products include construction sign plates and marker products, temporary barriers, security lights and warning lights, and other safety products. As of April 30, 2014, the Company had two subsidiaries.

NANYO CORPORATION is a general machinery trading company distributing and renting various machineries. The Company operates in three business segments. The Construction Machinery segment is involved in the sale of construction machinery, industrial vehicles and others, the leasing of construction machinery, the purchase and sale of used construction machinery and industrial vehicles. The Industrial Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of industrial equipment, as well as the purchase, sale and sale brokerage of industrial equipment. The Crushed Stone segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of crushed stones. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had nine subsidiaries and one associated company.

Marukyo Corporation is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the retail business. Along with its subsidiary, the Company operates in two business segments. The Retailing segment is engaged in the retail of general food products, perishable food products, daily necessities and other products through the operation of supermarkets. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate to tenants. As of September 30, 2014, the Company had one domestic consolidated subsidiary.

WASHHOUSE CO.,LTD. is a Japan-based company engaged in provision of coin-operated laundry system. The Company's business mainly includes franchise (FC) business, store management business and company-operated stores business. As the chain headquarters of the coin-operated laundry, FC business provides a FC system to FC owner. Store management business engages in management and operation of FC stores. Company-operated business engages in management of company-operated stores.

TOHO Co., Ltd. is mainly engaged in the sale of food products. The Distributor segment is engaged in the direct delivery and sales of commercial food to food-service industries including theme parks, hotels, restaurants and offices. The Cash & Carry segment is engaged in the cash sale of commercial food to small- and medium-sized catering service providers. The Food Supermarket segment operates supermarkets focused on fresh food. The Others segment is involved in the provision of quality control services, integrated construction contract business, as well as the leasing of real estate and others. As of January 31, 2015, the Company had 30 subsidiaries and one associated company.

Mitsui High-tec, Inc. is engaged in the manufacturing of mold too, electronic parts, industrial machinery and machine tool. The Company operates in four business segments. The Mold Tool segment provides cutting dies for motor core products and other precision mold for various components. The Electronic Parts segment provides integrated circuit (IC) lead frames and IC assembly parts. The Industrial Machinery segment provides motor core products. The Machine Tool segment provides surface grinders. Its overseas operating locations are in Singapore, Hong Kong, Malaysia, Philippines, Thailand, Taiwan, Mainland China and the United States. As of January 31, 2013, the Company had 15 subsidiaries.

Shochiku Co., Ltd. is mainly engaged in the image business. The Image-related segment is engaged in the production, purchase, sale, distribution and performance of theater movies, the operation of movie theaters and theater shops, the production and sale of television (TV) movies, the planning and production of commercials, the software production, editing and broadcasting for communications satellite and cable TV, and the manufacture, purchase and sale of video software. The Drama segment plans, produces and performs dramas and dispatches actors. The Real Estate segment leases its own properties. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture, purchase, sale and leasing of stage costumes, the production and sale of programs, the planning and sale of character goods, the production and sale of drama stage props and audios, the development and licensing of music copyrights, the management and cleaning of real estate. On February 27, 2014, it sold a propeerty.

YASKAWA Electric Corporation is mainly engaged in the manufacture, sale, installation, maintenance and engineering of electrical equipment. The Motion Control segment's products include alternating current (AC) turbo motors, general inverters, high-speed motors and machine controllers. The Robot segment mainly offers arc welding robots, spot welding robots, painting robots, handling robots and other robots. The System Engineering segment offers electric systems for steel plants, electrical instrumentation systems for sewages, electrical instrumentation systems for various industries and others. The Others segment offers information-related products and services, office automation (OA) equipment, information processing software and services, logistics and others. As of March 20, 2014, the Company had 79 subsidiaries and 26 associated companies.

HOPE, INC. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in public private sharing (PPS) business, which supports the self- financial resources of local governments. It provides three services. Financial resources support services include dead space service and media creation service. Operating activities support services include sales agency service and marketing research service. Information platform service publishes the information media in i Publicity Papers.

IINO KAIUN KAISHA, LTD. is a company primarily engaged in the shipping business. The Company operates through three business segments. The Overseas Shipping segment is engaged in the shipping, ship leasing, ship chartering and management, as well as ship brokerage business, the sale of ship equipment and the operation of ship agencies. The Coastal Shipping segment is engaged in the shipping, ship leasing, ship chartering and management. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing and management of buildings, warehousing business and real estate related business.

Toyota Motor Corporation (Toyota) conducts business in the automotive industry. The Company also conducts business in finance and other industries. The Company's segments include Automotive, Financial Services and All Other. Toyota sells its vehicles in approximately 190 countries and regions. Toyota's markets for its automobiles are Japan, North America, Europe and Asia. The Company's Automotive segment includes the design, manufacture, assembly and sale of passenger vehicles, minivans and commercial vehicles, such as trucks and related parts and accessories. The Company's Financial Services segment consists of providing financing to dealers and their customers for the purchase or lease of Toyota vehicles. The All Other segment includes the design, manufacturing and sale of housing, telecommunications and other businesses. Its information technology related businesses include a Web portal for automobile information called GAZOO.com.

DAIICHI KOUTSU SANGYO Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in taxi, bus, real estate, finance and other businesses. The Company operates in six segments. The Taxi segment operates taxis, nursing care taxis, sleeping cars, jumbo taxis, hired cars and others. The Bus segment operates reserved and route buses. The Real Estate Subdivision segment is engaged in the planning and sale of family condominium buildings, as well as the sale of detached houses. The Real Estate Leasing segment is involved in the rental and management of food buildings and residential buildings. The Finance segment is engaged in the provision of real estate mortgage loans and the regeneration of properties. The Others segment is involved in the repair and maintenance of automobiles, the sale of liquefied petroleum gas (LPG), the parking business and other businesses.

Kyushu Financial Group Inc is a Japan-based company principally engaged in banking businesses. The Company operates through three segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the deposits, loans, securities investment, domestic and foreign exchanges businesses, as well as the counter sale of investment trust and insurance products, among others. The Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing and lending businesses. The Others segment is engaged in the credit card and credit guarantee business, the entrusted calculation and software development businesses, debt guarantee business, the investigation and research of finance and economics, as well as the management consulting business, among others.

NISSO PRONITY Co., Ltd. is engaged in the processing and sale of manufacturing materials including raw materials, unit components and consumable materials mainly used in automobile, home appliance and other manufacturing industries. The Company operates in three business segments. The Customized Processed Product segment provides custom-made products, including panels for clean rooms, heat insulating panels for temporary houses, photovoltaic generation trestles, as well as components for automobile manufacturing lines, semiconductors, coin-operated parking systems and wind-power generation. The Planned Product segment is engaged in the planning, processing and sale of mass-produced products, including metal slates and deck plates, copper and stainless steel products, construction roofs and wall materials, as well as livestock and gardening materials. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of contract-based processing services, the delivery of products and others.

YAMAE HISANO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the food-related business. The Company has four business segments. The Food-related segment is engaged in the sale of general processed food, alcohol products and frozen food, the manufacture of distilled spirits and box lunches, as well as the manufacture, processing and sale of farm and marine products. The Sweetened Powder-, Feed and Livestock-related segment sells food materials, feeds, animal products and sea food. The Housing- and Real Estate-related segment is engaged in the sale of home building materials, household equipment and wood building materials, as well as the rental of real estate. The Others segment is involved in the insurance, transportation, fuel-related, car rental and information processing businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 17 subsidiaries and one associated company.

Fukuoka Financial Group, Inc. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the banking business. The Company has one business segments. The Banking business is engaged in the provision of banking services, such as deposit, loan, domestic and foreign exchange, among others. The Others business is engaged in the guarantee business, the business revitalization support business, the loan management and collection businesses, as well as other banking businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 19 consolidated subsidiaries.

The Miyazaki Bank, Ltd. (the Bank) is a regional bank that operates in two segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the provision of financial services such as deposit business, lending business, domestic exchange business, foreign exchange business and other related services. The Leasing segment is involved in the general leasing business. In addition, the Bank is also engaged in the investment to stocks and corporate bonds, the management consulting business, credit guarantee business such as mortgage, and the credit card business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries.

Kyushu Electric Power Company, Incorporated is a Japan-based company mainly involved in the electric power business. It has four business segments. The Electric Power segment offers electric power that the Company generated and purchased from other energy supplier. The Energy-related segment is engaged in the wholesale of thermal electric power, the research, design, construction and supervision of electric- and civil engineering-related construction work, as well as the environment protection for power plants. This segment is also involved in the sale of electric machine tools, natural uranium, gas and liquefied natural gas (LNG), and the new energy generation and heat supply businesses. The Information Communications segment offers data communication, broadband, fixed phone and information technology (IT)-related services. The Others segment is involved in the environmental, recycling, real estate, housing-related service and nursing care businesses.

Kawasaki Kisen Kaisha, Ltd. is primarily engaged in the marine transportation business. The Company operates in three business segments. The Containership segment is engaged in the operation of containerships shipping and logistics business. The Unscheduled Carrier segment is engaged in the operation of dry bulk transportation business, car carrier business, energy transportation business, costal water and domestic shipping businesses. The Marine Resource Development and Heavy-Lift Ship segment is engaged in the operation of energy-related development business, offshore support vessel business, and heavy-lift ship business. The Others is engaged in the operation of ship management, travel agency, real estate leasing and management businesses, among others.

THE OITA BANK, LTD. (the Bank) is a regional bank mainly engaged in the provision of financial services. The Bank operates in three business segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the provision of deposit, loan, security trading and investment, domestic and foreign exchange, futures transactions, bonds underwriting and registration services. The Leasing segment is engaged in the provision of leasing services. The Others segment is involved in credit card, credit guarantee, computer-related business, investment and financing businesses.

HASEGAWA CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the religious product related business. The Company is involved in the retail and wholesale of Buddhist altars and fittings, the sale of gravestones, the contracted construction work of inner shrines for Buddhist temples, the restoration of cultural properties, the design, planning and sales agency of charnel houses, as well as the provision of funeral consulting services and funeral director referral services, among others. The Company has three segments, which including Eastern Japan segment, Western Japan segment and Temple Related segment. Through its subsidiary, the Company is also engaged in the manufacture of Buddhist altars and fittings, the design of inner shrines for Buddhist temples and others.

ZENRIN CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the production and sale of the database of maps. The Company operates in three business segments. The Map Database-related segment is engaged in the manufacture, printing and sale of residential maps, application maps, Internet service related map data, residential map database, as well as the investigation, character input/output, production and distribution of car navigation data, three dimensional (3D) map data and other map data, the provision of smart phone and cell phone services. The General Printing Related segment is engaged in the manufacture, sale, emendation and character input/output of general printed materials. The Others segment is engaged in the sale of purchased goods, the design, development and operation of digital signage and Internet business.

The Minami-Nippon Bank, Ltd. (the Bank) operates in two business segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the deposit, loan, securities investment, domestic and foreign exchange and other related business. The Others segment is involved in the leasing business, as well as the provision of delivery and security services of cash. As of March 31, 2014, the Bank had one subsidiary and one associated company.

ROYAL HOLDINGS Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the restaurant business, contract business, in-flight meal business, hotel business and food business, among others. The Restaurant segment operates chain restaurants, such as hospitality restaurant chain Royal Host, as well as beer restaurants, cafeterias and other specialty restaurants. The Contract segment provides various dining services to customers in airport terminal buildings, expressway service areas, large size commercial facilities, departments, office buildings, nursing facilities and golf courses. The In-flight Food segment provides in-flight meal services to Fukuoka, Kansai and Narita airports. The Hotel segment operates nationwide hotels under the name of Richmond Hotel. The Food segment manufactures and sells food products for the Restaurant segment and the Contract segment. The Company is also engages in the sale of food, and the leasing of real estates.

SANKYU INC. is a Japan-based company that is principally involved in the logistics business. The Logistics segment is engaged in the loading and unloading of marine vessels' goods, the operation of container terminals, as well as the provision of packaging, storage and management of warehouses, and transportation services, among others. The Machinery Works segment specializes in the construction, installation, pipe working and maintenance of general industrial machinery and environmental equipment, the transportation of large and heavy goods, the design, assembly and construction of bridges, as well as the construction of factory facilities. The Others segment is involved in the provision of services related to information systems, manpower-dispatching, insurance agency, welfare and civil engineering, the construction of plants, as well as the leasing, maintenance and management of machinery. On June 28, 2013, it acquired a 100% stake in Japan Industrial Testing Co., Ltd.

Joyfull Co., Ltd. is engaged in the operation of family restaurant chain under the name Joyfull with a focus on Western foods menu. The Company offers grilled foods, light meal, hamburgers, steaks, set meals, salads, pasta, curry rice, desserts and drinks, among others. The restaurants are located in the Northern Kyushu, Southern Kyushu, Chugoku, Shikoku, Kinki, Chubu, Kanto, Hokuriku and Tohoku areas. Through its subsidiary, the Company is also engaged in the insurance agency business and temporary staffing business. As of December 31, 2013, the Company had one subsidiary.

HouseFreedom Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the real estate business. The Company operates in four business segments. The Real Estate Brokerage segment is involved in the brokerage for real estate trading in Osaka and Fukuoka Prefecture, as well as the collection of real estate information. The Newly Constructed House Sales segment is engaged in the sale of new houses, as well as the construction management and the sale of newly built houses. The Construction Contract Work segment is involved in the contract works for custom-built house and standardized house construction, as well as renovation services. The Non-Life Insurance segment provides real estate-related insurance agency services covering fire disaster and earthquake, among others. On October 1, 2013, the Company merged with a wholly owned subsidiary. On December 9, 2013, the Company acquired Osaka-based company. On May 28, 2014, the Company established an Osaka-based subsidiary.

RIX CORPORATION is a Japan-based equipment manufacturing company. The Company operates in six business segments. The Pressure Generator segment manufactures and sells high-pressure and hydraulic pumps, plunger pumps, submersible pumps and spiral pumps. The Applied Equipment and System Product segment manufactures and sells precision aqueous cleaning equipment and high-pressure aqueous cleaning equipment. The Ancillary Equipment and Component segment manufactures and sells rotary joints, multijoints, oil seals, circulating nozzles and filters. The Related Technology Product segment manufactures and sells piston valves, bulbs, vacuum pumps and compressors. The Precious Automatic and Measuring Equipment segment manufactures and sells testing equipment and inverters. The Others segment manufactures and sells synthetic resin products, sub-materials for steel making, as well as environment-related equipment, among others.

MR MAX CORPORATION is a Japan-based company engaged in the retail business. Through Internet and its stores, the Company sells household electrical appliances including video equipment such as televisions, audio, communication equipment, refrigerators, washing machines, illumination equipment and air conditioners, among others; apparel products including clothes for babies, children, men and women, shoes, sundry goods, watches and jewelries, among others; living life products including pet accessories, bicycles, sports products, car supplies, toys, stationery, garden and do it yourself (DIY) supplies, kitchen accessories, daily sundry goods, interior and storage accessories; health and beauty care (HBC)products including detergents, cosmetics, tissues and medicines; as well as foods including confectionery, drinks, processed food, rice, alcoholic beverage and other day delivery food.

BEST DENKI CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the sale of home electric appliances and information communication equipment. The Company has five business segments. The Electrical Home Appliance Retail segment is involved in the retail of electrical home appliances and information communications equipment. The Electrical Home Appliance Wholesale segment sells electrical home appliances and information communications equipment to franchisees. The Credit segment is involved in the consumer loan business. The Service segment provides repair, delivery and other post-sale services. The Others segment is engaged in the construction, expansion and renovation of stores and houses, the sale of land and buildings, the provision of temporary staffing services, the printing and printmaking businesses, as well as the insurance business. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had 10 subsidiaries and three associated companies.

Sumitomo Corporation is an integrated trading company. The Company is engaged in trading a range of goods and commodities, and in various business activities. It operates through five business segments: Metal Products, which includes various metal products, such as steel products and non-ferrous metal products; Transportation & Construction Systems, which is engaged in transactions involving ships, aircrafts, transportation systems, motor vehicles, construction equipment, and related components and parts; Environment & Infrastructure, which is engaged in a range of overseas infrastructure development projects, such as power generation, and Procurement and Construction (EPC); Media, Network, Lifestyle Related Goods & Services, which is engaged in cable television (TV) operations and movie business, among others, and Mineral Resources, Energy, Chemical & Electronics, which is engaged in the development and trading of mineral and energy resources and commodity derivative transactions.

The Chikuho Bank, Ltd. (the Bank) operates in three business segments. The Banking segment is engaged in the deposits, loans, domestic and foreign exchange businesses. This segment is also engaged in the securities investment business, trust business, as well as the over-the-counter sale of public bonds, securities investment trust and insurance goods. The Leasing segment provides leasing services. The Others segment provides debts guarantee services. As of March 31, 2013, the Bank had four consolidated subsidiaries.

Amaze Co.,Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the operation of hotels. The Company operates its business in two business segments. The Hotel Accommodation segment involves in the operation of hotels equipped with guest rooms, banquet and meeting rooms, as well as the provison of catering services. This segment operates hotels under brands named HOTEL AZ and Kamenoi Hotel. The Restaurant segment involves in the operation of restaurants.

Nishi-Nippon Railroad Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based transportation company. The Company operates in six business segments. The Transportation segment operates railroad, bus, taxi and other transportation-related businesses. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing and allotment sale of real estate properties, as well as other real estate-related businesses. The Distribution segment is involved in the store business. The Logistics segment is involved in the international and domestic logistics businesses. The Leisure and Service segment is involved in the hotel, leisure, travel, restaurant, advertising agency and other businesses. The Others segment is engaged in the integrated circuit (IC) card, automobile maintenance-related, construction and metal recycle businesses.

Platz Co Ltd is engaged in the manufacturing and sale of nursing care beds, mattresses and other bed related items. The Company involved in the planning, developing, design and wholesale of nursing care beds, mattresses and other bed related items. Through its subsidiary it also engaged in assembly and quality checking of nursing care beds. Its products include beds for home uses and beds for facilities use.

Fukuoka REIT Corporation is real estate investment trust (REIT) company. It aims to achieve sustainable growth in asset and stable earnings from mid- to long-term perspectives. The Company mainly invests in commercial facilities, office buildings, hotels, residences and other facilities in Fukuoka city and neighboring areas, as well as major cities in Japan. Its property portfolio includes Canal City Hakata, Canal City Hakata B, Park Place Oita, Canal City Business Center Building, Gofukumachi Business Center, Taihaku Street Business Center, SunLiveCity Kokura, Higashi-Hie Business Center, AEON Hara Shopping Center and Square Mall Kagoshima Usuki. The asset manager of the Fund is Fukuoka Realty Corporation Limited. On March 1, 2013, the Trust acquired a residential property and a hotel property, which were located in Fukuoka city and Oita city, respectively. On March 28, 2013, it acquired a property in Fukuoka. On March 28, 2014, it acquired a logistics center located in Saga.

The Miyazaki Taiyo Bank, Ltd. operates in three business divisions. The Banking division is involved in the loans, deposits, domestic and foreign exchange, as well as other related businesses. The Leasing and Guarantee division is engaged in the general leasing business and personal loans guarantee business. The Others division is engaged in the provision of accounting, consolidation, collection and delivery of cash and others, as well as the venture capital business. As of March 31, 2014, the Bank had three consolidated subsidiaries.

Media Five Co. is primarily engaged in supplying IT engineers and business outsourcing services related to software development. The B to B Solutions Group segment provides IT engineers such as programmers and system engineers, as well as business support services. Its businesses include programming, network building, as well as maintenance and operation services, and others. The B to C Solutions Group provides contract software development for systems required by customers, maintenance and operation services, and also provides servers. The School segment operates school engaged in IT professional training on contracts with other companies, and also for the Company. The Construction segment provides construction design and management, construction work, interior and exterior work, and others. As of May 31, 2013, the Company had one subsidiary.

Canon Inc. (Canon) is a manufacturer of office multifunction devices (MFDs), plain paper copying machines, laser printers, inkjet printers, cameras and lithography equipment. Canon sells its products principally under the Canon brand name and through sales subsidiaries. Each of these subsidiaries is responsible for marketing and distribution to retail dealers in an assigned territory. Canon operates its business in three segments: the Office Business Unit, the Imaging System Business Unit, and the Industry and Others Business Unit. Canon's research and development activities range from basic research to product-oriented research directed at maintaining Canon's technological operations in the marketplace. Canon has manufacturing subsidiaries in a range of countries, including the United States, Germany, France, the Netherlands, Taiwan, China, Malaysia, Thailand, Vietnam and the Philippines.

RKB MAINICHI HOLDINGS CORPORATION, formerly RKB Mainichi Broadcasting Corporation is a company mainly engaged in the broadcasting, system-related and real estate businesses. Along with its subsidiaries, the Company operates in four business segments. The Broadcasting segment is engaged in the provision of broadcasting services of sponsored paid programs and commercial messages (CMs) broadcasting services, as well as the production of television (TV) programs and the provision of production staff dispatching services for TV program production. The System-related segment develops, sells and maintains software, as well as dispatches system engineers. The Real Estate segment leases and manages real estate, as well as provides cleaning services and operates parking lots. The Others segment is engaged in the production of industrial movies and film bulletins, the provision of staff dispatching service, as well as the planning of events.

THE FUKUOKA CHUO BANK, LTD. is primarily engaged in retail banking business. It is engaged in depositary, lending, domestic and foreign exchange businesses. In addition, it is also involved in agency business, counter sales of public bonds such as government bonds and securities investment trusts, counter sales of insurance products, and other business.

Mitsui & Co., Ltd. is engaged in the product sales, logistics and financing, as well as the development of international infrastructure and other projects. The Company's segments include Iron & Steel Products, Mineral & Metal Resources, Machinery & Infrastructure, Chemicals, Energy, Lifestyle, Innovation & Corporate Development, Americas, EMEA (Europe, the Middle East and Africa) and Asia Pacific. The Company holds projects in a range of fields, such as iron and steel products, mineral and metal resources, infrastructure projects, integrated transportation systems, chemicals, energy, food, food and retail management, healthcare and service, consumer business, information technology (IT) and communication business and corporate development business. The Company's segments are engaged in procurement and supply of iron and steel products, Internet infrastructure business and supply of social infrastructure, among others.

HEIWA REAL ESTATE CO., LTD. is a Japan-based real estate company that is active in four business segments. The Leasing segment specializes in the development, leasing, management and operation of stock exchanges, offices, commercial facilities and housing. The Real Estate Development segment is engaged in the development and management of real estate, as well as real estate agency business. The Housing Development segment involves in the development and distribution of residential real estates. The Others segment is engaged in the maintenance and repair of building equipment, insurance agency business, as well as the operation of nursing homes with nursing care services. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had nine consolidated subsidiaries.

Mitsubishi Heavy Industries, Ltd. is a diversified manufacturer. The Energy and Environment segment offers boilers, turbines, gas turbines, diesel engines, water wheels, windmills, nuclear power equipments, nuclear power peripheral devices, among others. The Traffic and Transportation segment offers various ships, including cruise ships, liquefied natural gas (LNG) ships, liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) ships, car ferry, special purpose vessels, automobile carriers, oil tankers, container ships and others, as well as marine structures, among others. The Defense and Space segment offers ships, fighters, helicopters, aircraft fuselage parts, defense aircraft engines, induction flying objects, torpedoes, among others. The Machinery and Equipment systems segment offers waste treatment and exhaust gas treatment equipments, transportation equipments, steel machinery, compressors, bridges, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 290 subsidiaries and 39 associated companies.
